	                                                <h1>Php laravel question</h1>
Laravel interview quiestion <br>
0) What is Laravel? <br>
Laravel is open-source web framework based on PHP.Laravel is free to use.It supports the MVC (Model-View-Controller) architectural pattern.
It is developed by Taylor Otwell.The first version of Laravel was released on 9th June 2011. <br>

1) What is MVC? <br>
when user sent http request by route it goes in controller then model after that database then it return in model then controller.
controller sent to in view.than user can see output.
*user request-->Routing->controller--><--model--><--database
                             |-->view
                             <br>
2) What are the main features of Laravel? <br>
Some of the main features of Laravel are: <br>
*Query builder <br>
*Reverse Routing <br>
*Restful Controllers <br>
*Migrations <br>
*Database Seeding <br>
*Unit Testing <br>
*Homestead <br>

3) What do you understand by Eloquent ORM? <br>
Eloquent ORM (Object-Relational Mapping) is one of the main features of the Laravel framework. <br>
It may be defined as an advanced PHP implementation of the active record pattern.
Active record pattern is an architectural pattern. <br>
*Eloquent হচ্ছে Database এর query এর জন্য একটি নতুন এবং advance কৌশল যা আপনার Database এর complex query এর জন্য সহজ syntax প্রদান করে

4) What is Query Builder in Laravel? <br>
Laravel's Query Builder provides more direct access to the database, alternative to the Eloquent ORM. <br>
 It doesn't require SQL queries to be written directly. <br>
 It offers a set of classes and methods which are capable of building queries programmatically. <br>

5)What are Some aggregates methods provides by the Laravel's query builder?
Some of the methods that Query Builder provides are: <br>

count() <br>
max() <br>
min() <br>
avg() <br>
sum() <br>

6) What is routing? <br>
All Laravel routes are defined in route files, which are stored in the routes directory. These files are loaded by the MVC framework.
Those routes are allotted as the web middleware group, which provide features such as session state and CSRF protection. <br>

7)What is MiddleWare? <br>
MiddleWare is a controller.It is used to protect Route. if user is authenticated,
 the middleware will allow to access otherwise middleware will not allow to access. <br>
 
8)PHP তে Anonymous function কি? <br>
 anonymous function মানে হচ্ছে নাম বিহীন function, সুতরাং PHP তে যখন কোনো function 
 declare বা ঘোষণা করা হয়, কিন্তু function টির কোনো নাম থাকেনা, PHP তে সেই function কে anonymous function বলে। <br>
 নোট : anonymous function অবশ্যই semi-colon (;) দিয়ে শেষ করতে হয়।
 PHP তে anonymous function কে array element and call back function হিসেবে ব্যবহার করা যাবে। <br>
 example <br>
 <?php
// Assign an anonymous function to a variable
$makeGreeting = function( $name, $timeOfDay ) {
  return "Good $timeOfDay, $name!";
}; <br>
echo $makeGreeting("Omran","Morning"); 
//Result: Good Morning Omran!
?> <br>

9)PHP তে closures কি ? <br>
closure হচ্ছে একটা object যা anonymous function কে represent করে । অন্য ভাবে বলা যায়,closure হচ্ছে 
anonymous function কে Object Oriented way তে ব্যবহার করার মাধ্যম।  <br>

10)PHP তে Lambda function কি? <br>
যখন একটি anonymous function অন্য একটা function এর argument হিসেবে pass হয়, তখন সেটিকে বলা হয় lambda function. <br>
example:
<?php
// Pass Lambda to function
function shout ($message){
  echo $message();
}
  
// Call function
shout(function(){
  return "Hello world";
});
?>

11)What type of Parameter??
*Required Parameters
*Optional Parameters
</p>
			<h1>Run Laravel project after downloading from github/gitlab</h1>
<p>
Step:
1. download or clone project </br>
2. Go to the folder application using cd </br>
3. Run composer install on your cmd or terminal </br>
4. Copy .env.example file to .env on root folder. </br>
    You can type copy .env.example .env if using command prompt Windows </br>
     or cp .env.example .env if using terminal Ubuntu</br>
5. Open your .env file and change the database name (DB_DATABASE)</br>
6. Run php artisan key:generate </br>
7. Run php artisan migrate </br>
8.Run php artisan serve</br>
</p>

                                          <h1>Laravel Routing</h1>

<p>
1.url('/') </br>
2.URL::to('about') </br>
example: Both are same </br>
route::get('/about','HomeController@home'); </br>
3."{{route('about')}}" </br>
* example:name route </br>
route::get('/about','HomeController@home')->name('about'); </br>	
route::get(md5('/about'),'HomeController@home')->name('about'); </br>
example: for encrypt use md5('/about') / encrypt('/about')                              
</p>


